Subscription-based revenue models are expected to continue dominating the online entertainment market as consumers increasingly opt for convenient on-demand content services. Platforms like Netflix and Amazon Prime Video are leading the market, leveraging their vast libraries of original and exclusive content. The popularity of video streaming services is driving significant growth in the video content segment, with streaming platforms investing heavily in content production to attract and retain subscribers.

